Preheat your oven to 220°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways and
scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm chunks
(no need to peel). Pop on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread in a single layer. Roast on
the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turn halfway.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil.
When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the
heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then
remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own
steam).

While the squash and rice cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on
medium high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with
salt and pepper. Cook until the chicken is browned on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Stir occasionally.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @spring onions{2}, slice
thinly and keep to the side. Once the chicken has browned, add the red onion and
cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Add in the garlic and @tandoori masala spice{1} (add less if you don't like heat).
Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, @water{500%ml} and
the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to
medium. Simmer until reduced by half, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the @baby spinach{100} in
handfuls, stir through and cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the
@soured cream{75%g}, stir into the sauce until combined, then remove from the
heat.

Add the roasted squash to the curry and stir everything together.

> TIP: Warm the curry through on a low heat if necessary, adding a splash of water
> if necessary. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} and spoon the curry on top. Sprinkle over the
spring onion and enjoy!